```diff
+         for i, message in enumerate(messages):
+             bubble_id = f&quot;{i:0{max_digits}d}&quot;
+             entry = create_bubble_entry(session_id, bubble_id, message, i)
+             bubble_entries.append((entry[&#39;key&#39;], entry[&#39;value&#39;]))
+         
+         # Insert bubbles
+         print(f&quot;üíæ Inserting bubbles into database...&quot;)
+         cursor.executemany(
+             &quot;INSERT OR REPLACE INTO cursorDiskKV (key, value) VALUES (?, ?);&quot;,
+             bubble_entries
+         )
+         conn.commit()
+         print(f&quot;‚úÖ Inserted {len(bubble_entries)} bubbles\n&quot;)
+         
+         # Rebuild composer index (includes ALL conversations, not just this one)
+         rebuild_composer_index(cursor)
+         conn.commit()
+         
+         # Verify
+         cursor.execute(f&quot;SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE &#39;bubbleId:{session_id}:%&#39;;&quot;)
+         restored_count = cursor.fetchone()[0]
+         
+         if restored_count == len(bubble_entries):
+             print(f&quot;\n‚úÖ Verification passed: {restored_count} bubbles in database&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;\nüéâ Conversation restored successfully!&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   Session ID: {session_id}&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   Messages: {len(messages)}&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   Backup saved to: {backup_path}&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;\nüìã Next steps:&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   1. Quit Cursor completely (Cmd+Q)&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   2. Wait 5 seconds&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   3. Reopen Cursor&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   4. Wait 1-2 minutes for indexing&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   5. Check chat history panel&quot;)
+             return True
+         else:
+             print(f&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  Verification warning: Expected {len(bubble_entries)}, found {restored_count}&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   Backup saved to: {backup_path}&quot;)
+             return False
+         
+     except Exception as e:
+         conn.rollback()
+         print(f&quot;‚ùå Error: {e}&quot;)
+         import traceback
+         traceback.print_exc()
+         print(f&quot;\nüíæ Backup saved to: {backup_path}&quot;)
+         print(&quot;   You can restore from backup if needed&quot;)
+         return False
+     finally:
+         conn.close()
+ 
+ if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:
+     if len(sys.argv) &lt; 2:
+         print(&quot;Usage: python3 restore_specstory_with_session_id.py &lt;specstory_file.md&gt; [--force]&quot;)
+         print(&quot;\nThis script:&quot;)
+         print(&quot;  1. Backs up your database BEFORE making changes&quot;)
+         print(&quot;  2. Generates a session ID if one doesn&#39;t exist in the file&quot;)
+         print(&quot;  3. Only modifies the specific conversation being imported&quot;)
+         print(&quot;  4. Rebuilds the composer index to include ALL conversations&quot;)
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     specstory_file = Path(sys.argv[1])
+     force = &#39;--force&#39; in sys.argv
+     
+     if not specstory_file.exists():
+         print(f&quot;‚ùå File not found: {specstory_file}&quot;)
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     print(f&quot;üìÑ Restoring: {specstory_file.name}&quot;)
+     if force:
+         print(&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  --force flag enabled: will replace existing conversation\n&quot;)
+     
+     # Check if Cursor is running
+     try:
+         result = subprocess.run([&#39;pgrep&#39;, &#39;-f&#39;, &#39;Cursor&#39;], capture_output=True, text=True)
+         if result.returncode == 0:
+             print(&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  WARNING: Cursor appears to be running!&quot;)
+             print(&quot;   The database may be locked. Consider closing Cursor first.\n&quot;)
+             if not force:
+                 print(&quot;   Use --force flag to proceed anyway (may fail if DB is locked)&quot;)
+                 sys.exit(1)
+             else:
+                 print(&quot;   Proceeding with --force flag...\n&quot;)
+         else:
+             print(&quot;‚úÖ Cursor is not running - safe to proceed\n&quot;)
+     except Exception as e:
+         print(f&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  Could not check if Cursor is running: {e}&quot;)
+         print(&quot;   Proceeding anyway...\n&quot;)
+     
+     success = restore_specstory_conversation(specstory_file, force=force)
+     
+     if not success:
+         print(&quot;\n‚ùå Restoration failed. Check errors above.&quot;)
+         sys.exit(1)
+ 
```

</details>

</tool-use>

    print(f'üîç Checking: {workspace_dir}')
    
    try:
        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(db_path))
        cursor = conn.cursor()

        cursor.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE ?', (f'%{session_id}%',))
        count = cursor.fetchone()[0]

            print(f'   ‚úÖ FOUND OUR SESSION: {count} entries!')
            # Get details
            cursor.execute('SELECT key FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE ? LIMIT 5', (f'%{session_id}%',))
            keys = [row[0] for row in cursor.fetchall()]
            for key in keys:
                print(f'      - {key[:80]}...')
        else:
            print(f'   ‚ùå Not found')
        
        conn.close()
    except Exception as e:
        print(f'   ‚ö†Ô∏è  Error: {e}')
    print()

```bash
python3 -c "
import sqlite3
import os
import glob
from pathlib import Path
import hashlib

# Current workspace
workspace_path = '/Users/fahadkiani/Desktop/development/crispr-assistant-main'
workspace_hash = hashlib.md5(workspace_path.encode()).hexdigest()

print(f'üìÅ Workspace: {workspace_path}')
print(f'üîë Hash: {workspace_hash}\n')

# Find workspace database
workspace_storage = Path.home() / 'Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage'
workspace_dbs = list(workspace_storage.glob('*/state.vscdb'))

print(f'üìã Found {len(workspace_dbs)} workspace databases\n')

# Our session ID
session_id = 'c8974909-e04c-4609-89d3-04a2545bcf2d'

# Check each database
for db_path in workspace_dbs:
    workspace_dir = db_path.parent.name
    print(f'üîç Checking: {workspace_dir}')
    
    try:
        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(db_path))
        cursor = conn.cursor()
        
        # Check for our session
        cursor.execute('SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE ?', (f'%{session_id}%',))
        count = cursor.fetchone()[0]
        
        if count > 0:
            print(f'   ‚úÖ FOUND OUR SESSION: {count} entries!')
            # Get details
            cursor.execute('SELECT key FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE ? LIMIT 5', (f'%{session_id}%',))
            keys = [row[0] for row in cursor.fetchall()]
            for key in keys:
                print(f'      - {key[:80]}...')
        else:
            print(f'   ‚ùå Not found')
        
        conn.close()
    except Exception as e:
        print(f'   ‚ö†Ô∏è  Error: {e}')
    print()
"
```

```diff
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Create a timestamped backup of the database.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     timestamp = datetime.now().strftime(&quot;%Y%m%d_%H%M%S&quot;)
+     backup_path = db_path.parent / f&quot;{db_path.name}.before_specstory_import_{timestamp}&quot;
+     shutil.copy2(db_path, backup_path)
+     print(f&quot;üíæ Database backed up to: {backup_path}&quot;)
+     return backup_path
+ 
+ def parse_specstory_markdown(file_path):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Parse SpecStory markdown and extract session ID and messages.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     with open(file_path, &#39;r&#39;, encoding=&#39;utf-8&#39;) as f:
+         content = f.read()
+     
+     # Try to extract session ID from header or generate one
+     session_match = re.search(r&#39;Session ([a-f0-9-]{36})&#39;, content)
+     if session_match:
+         session_id = session_match.group(1)
+         print(f&quot;‚úÖ Found session ID in file: {session_id}&quot;)
+     else:
+         # Generate a new session ID
+         session_id = str(uuid.uuid4())
+         print(f&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  No session ID found in file. Generated new ID: {session_id}&quot;)
+     
+     # Parse messages - format is: _**User (timestamp)**_ or _**Agent (model, mode)**_
+     messages = []
+     
+     # Find all message markers
+     pattern = r&#39;_\*\*User.*?\*\*_|_\*\*Agent.*?\*\*_|_\*\*Assistant.*?\*\*_&#39;
+     matches = list(re.finditer(pattern, content))
+     
+     if not matches:
+         print(&quot;‚ö†Ô∏è  No message markers found in file&quot;)
+         return session_id, []
+     
+     print(f&quot;‚úÖ Found {len(matches)} message markers&quot;)
+     
+     # Extract text for each message
+     for i, match in enumerate(matches):
+         is_user = &#39;User&#39; in match.group(0)
+         start_pos = match.end()
+         
+         # Find the end of this message (next marker or end of content)
+         if i + 1 &lt; len(matches):
+             end_pos = matches[i + 1].start()
+         else:
+             end_pos = len(content)
+         
+         # Extract the text
+         text = content[start_pos:end_pos]
+         
+         # Clean up the text
+         text = text.strip()
+         # Remove leading --- separators
+         text = re.sub(r&#39;^---+\s*&#39;, &#39;&#39;, text, flags=re.MULTILINE)
+         # Remove tool-use tags (but keep the text before them)
+         text = re.sub(r&#39;&lt;tool-use.*?&lt;/tool-use&gt;&#39;, &#39;&#39;, text, flags=re.DOTALL)
+         # Remove details tags
+         text = re.sub(r&#39;&lt;details&gt;.*?&lt;/details&gt;&#39;, &#39;&#39;, text, flags=re.DOTALL)
+         # Remove diff blocks
+         text = re.sub(r&#39;&#96;&#96;&#96;diff.*?&#96;&#96;&#96;&#39;, &#39;&#39;, text, flags=re.DOTALL)
+         # Remove multiple blank lines
+         text = re.sub(r&#39;\n{3,}&#39;, &#39;\n\n&#39;, text)
+         text = text.strip()
+         
+         # Only add if there&#39;s actual text content
+         if text and len(text) &gt; 10:  # At least 10 chars to avoid empty messages
+             if is_user:
+                 messages.append({&#39;type&#39;: &#39;user&#39;, &#39;text&#39;: text})
+             else:
+                 messages.append({&#39;type&#39;: &#39;assistant&#39;, &#39;text&#39;: text})
+     
+     return session_id, messages
+ 
+ def create_bubble_entry(conversation_id, bubble_id, message, index):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Create a bubble entry in Cursor&#39;s format.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     timestamp_ms = int(datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000) + (index * 1000)
+     
+     if message[&#39;type&#39;] == &#39;user&#39;:
+         bubble_data = {
+             &quot;_v&quot;: 3,
+             &quot;type&quot;: 0,  # 0 = user message
+             &quot;text&quot;: message[&#39;text&#39;],
+             &quot;bubbleId&quot;: bubble_id,
+             &quot;timestamp&quot;: timestamp_ms,
+             &quot;approximateLintErrors&quot;: [],
+             &quot;approximateLintWarnings&quot;: []
+         }
+     else:
+         bubble_data = {
+             &quot;_v&quot;: 3,
+             &quot;type&quot;: 1,  # 1 = assistant message
+             &quot;text&quot;: message[&#39;text&#39;],
+             &quot;bubbleId&quot;: bubble_id,
+             &quot;timestamp&quot;: timestamp_ms,
+             &quot;approximateLintErrors&quot;: [],
+             &quot;approximateLintWarnings&quot;: []
+         }
+     
+     return json.dumps(bubble_data)
+ 
+ def restore_to_workspace(specstory_file, workspace_path, dry_run=False):
+     &quot;&quot;&quot;Restore SpecStory conversation to workspace-specific database.&quot;&quot;&quot;
+     
+     # Find workspace database
+     db_path = find_workspace_database(workspace_path)
+     if not db_path:
+         print(f&quot;‚ùå Could not find workspace database&quot;)
+         return False
+     
+     # Check if database is locked (Cursor is running)
+     try:
+         test_conn = sqlite3.connect(str(db_path), timeout=1.0)
+         test_conn.close()
+     except sqlite3.OperationalError as e:
+         if &quot;locked&quot; in str(e).lower():
+             print(f&quot;‚ùå Database is locked! Please close Cursor completely before running this script.&quot;)
+             print(f&quot;   Database: {db_path}&quot;)
+             return False
+         raise
+     
+     if dry_run:
+         print(f&quot;üîç DRY RUN: Would restore to: {db_path}&quot;)
+         return True
+     
+     # Backup database
+     backup_path = backup_database(db_path)
+     
+     # Parse SpecStory file
+     session_id, messages = parse_specstory_markdown(specstory_file)
+     
+     if not messages:
+         print(&quot;‚ùå No messages found in SpecStory file&quot;)
+         return False
+     
+     print(f&quot;üìù Parsed {len(messages)} messages&quot;)
+     
+     # Connect to database
+     conn = sqlite3.connect(str(db_path))
+     cursor = conn.cursor()
+     
+     try:
+         # Check if cursorDiskKV table exists
+         cursor.execute(&quot;SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type=&#39;table&#39; AND name=&#39;cursorDiskKV&#39;&quot;)
+         if not cursor.fetchone():
+             print(&quot;‚ùå cursorDiskKV table not found in workspace database&quot;)
+             return False
+         
+         # Generate conversation ID
+         conversation_id = f&quot;conversation:{session_id}&quot;
+         
+         # Insert bubbles
+         bubbles_inserted = 0
+         for i, message in enumerate(messages):
+             bubble_id = f&quot;{session_id}-{i:04d}&quot;
+             bubble_key = f&quot;bubble:{session_id}:{bubble_id}&quot;
+             bubble_value = create_bubble_entry(conversation_id, bubble_id, message, i)
+             
+             # Insert or replace bubble
+             cursor.execute(
+                 &quot;INSERT OR REPLACE INTO cursorDiskKV (key, value) VALUES (?, ?)&quot;,
+                 (bubble_key, bubble_value)
+             )
+             bubbles_inserted += 1
+         
+         # Create composerData entry
+         composer_data = {
+             &quot;sessionId&quot;: session_id,
+             &quot;title&quot;: Path(specstory_file).stem.replace(&quot;_&quot;, &quot; &quot;).title(),
+             &quot;createdAt&quot;: int(datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000),
+             &quot;updatedAt&quot;: int(datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000)
+         }
+         
+         composer_key = f&quot;composerData:{session_id}&quot;
+         cursor.execute(
+             &quot;INSERT OR REPLACE INTO ItemTable (key, value) VALUES (?, ?)&quot;,
+             (composer_key, json.dumps(composer_data))
+         )
+         
+         # Commit
+         conn.commit()
+         
+         print(f&quot;‚úÖ Successfully restored {bubbles_inserted} messages to workspace database&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   Session ID: {session_id}&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   Database: {db_path}&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   Backup: {backup_path}&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;\nüìã Next steps:&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   1. Close Cursor completely (Cmd+Q)&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   2. Reopen Cursor&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   3. The restored conversation should appear in your chat history&quot;)
+         
+         return True
+         
+     except Exception as e:
+         conn.rollback()
+         print(f&quot;‚ùå Error during restoration: {e}&quot;)
+         print(f&quot;   Restoring from backup...&quot;)
+         shutil.copy2(backup_path, db_path)
+         return False
+     finally:
+         conn.close()
+ 
+ if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:
+     if len(sys.argv) &lt; 2:
+         print(&quot;Usage: python3 restore_specstory_to_workspace.py &lt;specstory_file&gt; [--dry-run]&quot;)
+         print(&quot;\nExample:&quot;)
+         print(&quot;  python3 restore_specstory_to_workspace.py .specstory/history/2025-11-19_17-33Z-designing-zero-tolerance-content-filtering-layer.md&quot;)
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     specstory_file = Path(sys.argv[1])
+     if not specstory_file.exists():
+         print(f&quot;‚ùå SpecStory file not found: {specstory_file}&quot;)
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     # Get current workspace path
+     workspace_path = Path.cwd()
+     
+     dry_run = &quot;--dry-run&quot; in sys.argv
+     
+     success = restore_to_workspace(specstory_file, workspace_path, dry_run=dry_run)
+     sys.exit(0 if success else 1)
+ 
```

</details>

                    print(f'   Sample key format: {sample[0][:100]}')

## Verification: data is in the database

The restoration worked:
- 93 bubbles inserted
- composerData entry created
- Session ID: `c31a0ca9-be18-4f33-b23c-0d1a4270520f`
- Database file touched to trigger refresh

## Why it might not appear

Cursor may need to re-index. Try:

1. Close Cursor completely (Cmd+Q ‚Äî not just the window)
2. Wait 5 seconds
3. Reopen Cursor
4. Look for: "2025-11-19 17-33Z-Designing-Zero-Tolerance-Content-Filtering-Layer"

If it still doesn't appear:
- Click "Chat History" in the sidebar
- Search for "zero-tolerance" or "content-filtering"
- Check for a "Load More" button at the bottom of chat history
- Try opening a file in the workspace, then check chat history again

## If it still doesn't show

This may be a Cursor limitation. The data is in the database, but Cursor may not display conversations restored this way. Options:
1. Export the conversation as a readable format (markdown/text)
